8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-215_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"5e1736fd-6a46-425f-96e3-3460f9fcb4f7","comments":[],"created_at":1783865956821808001,"creation_channel":"unknown","deps":[{"link_uuid":"93c2969d-6482-4249-b794-1de6d4b079d5","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"0435-8dce-4e9f-4121"}],"description":"## Reproduction Steps\n`bash scripts/probe-rebar.sh </dev/null` (non-interactive, as CI runs) → `PROBE RESULT: 37 passed, 103 failed` because the probe relies on rebar AUTO-INIT, which refuses without a TTY (`src/rebar/_cli/_init.py:62` gate). Adding an explicit `rebar init` to the isolated setup gets it to `130 passed, 10 failed`.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: the golden-path probe runs green non-interactively so it can be a CI smoke.\n- Actual: (a) needs a TTY for its store init; (b) 10 rotted assertions even after an explicit init:\n  - 2 stale key-set assertions: rebar `list` now emits `managed_refs` and `show` emits `digest_freshness`, which the probe's exact-key checks don't expect.\n  - 8 lifecycle-`--output json` assertions (claim/transition/reopen/delete) fail with an EMPTY id — the `LCID` capture from `create --output json` (probe line ~270) returns empty in this env, so downstream ops get `''`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `bash scripts/probe-rebar.sh </dev/null` exits 0 (runs non-interactively): add an explicit `rebar init` to the isolated setup (auto-init needs a TTY).\n- [ ] The `list`/`show` key-set assertions account for `managed_refs`/`digest_freshness`.\n- [ ] The lifecycle-`--output json` section captures a non-empty id from `create --output json`.\n- [ ] The probe is then wired into CI (the `golden-path` job in test.yml + gerrit-verify.yaml) so it can't silently rot.\n\n## Notes\nDiscovered while implementing ticket 0435 (README golden-path CI gate). 0435's clean-install golden-path is served by the NEW `scripts/check_readme_quickstart.py` (which runs `rebar init` explicitly and passes non-interactively); wiring the broader probe was deferred here because its pre-existing rot is out of the docs-remediation epic's scope.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"ff5902b4-200a-46fe-86fd-6d3dd959c80f","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"6cca-758d-38aa-4c23","ticket_type":"bug","title":"scripts/probe-rebar.sh: non-interactive-incompatible + 10 rotted assertions (not CI-runnable)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["3a4b3aea-2f36-4e81-a304-436c800a8f12","acfa8291-d073-4ab2-9632-517bd78bb16a","93c2969d-6482-4249-b794-1de6d4b079d5","ff5902b4-200a-46fe-86fd-6d3dd959c80f","ce190361-d447-466c-822d-2613c3da0421","a0b30888-eb5d-4825-aae8-416a8469aa3a"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784487883325371403,"uuid":"b496dac1-5590-419c-bc3e-df8d6370bb0f"}